Learning AI can be a challenging but rewarding process. Here are some steps you can take to get started:

Develop a solid foundation in computer science and mathematics. This includes topics like algorithms, data structures, linear algebra, calculus, probability theory, and statistics.

Familiarize yourself with programming languages commonly used in AI, such as Python, R, and Java.

Learn about the different subfields of AI, such as machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, computer vision, and robotics.

Take online courses and tutorials to learn the basics of AI and related technologies. There are many resources available online, such as edX, Coursera, and Udacity.

Build projects to practice your skills and gain practical experience. This can include working on open-source projects, creating your own projects, and participating in hackathons.

Stay up-to-date with the latest research and advancements in the field by reading academic papers, attending conferences, and following industry leaders on social media.

Remember that learning AI is a continuous process and requires dedication and hard work. With persistence and effort, however, you can develop the skills and knowledge needed to become proficient in AI.
